article.description: — Wayne Bristol Jr.'s 14 points helped Georgetown defeat Merrimack 69-67 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Georgetown takes down Merrimack 69-67
article.story: WASHINGTON -- — Wayne Bristol Jr.'s 14 points helped Georgetown defeat Merrimack 69-67 on Wednesday night. Bristol added three blocks for the Hoyas (5-2). Supreme Cook scored 12 points and added 12 rebounds. Jayden Epps had 11 points and was 3 of 7 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 4 from the line. Jordan Derkack finished with 22 points, seven rebounds and three steals for the Warriors (3-5). Adam Clark added 11 points and three steals for Merrimack. Samba Diallo also had nine points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
